Description: Fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows two flat areas joined by a convex rounded area like from a bag or suchlike (similar to EA86732, EA86742, EA86756 and EA86762). Two impressions of a turned string in the break with a width of 0.2 cm. The convex top shows finger impressions a a small complete but slightly squashed impression of an oval scarab-like seal. It is cut very sharply with very small signs. Visible are three rows of three signs each. The top row shows a seated figure of Amun in the middle, the second a seated baboon.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
